description.narrative: Partnership remains one of the strong pillars for the success of all Social and Behavioral Change interventions and reflects the effective involvement and commitment of communities. For 2021, multiple agreements between the government and civil society organizations (URAC, REVOCAP, GNU, ROCBACS...) have been facilitated and encouraged by UNICEF as part of the response to emergencies (COVID-19, Polio, Ebola). In addition, the youth-adolescent focus, through several organizations or networks (Young Voices of the Sahel, Consortium Jeunesse Senegal, Young Volunteers for Environment, Social Change Factory, DECLIC, CONAFE) prompted a strengthening of collaboration, particularly on digital, for the benefit of the child. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:01/02/2022
